Very poor customer service.  There have been a couple instances I have made orders for our "house" account and have gotten defensive responses. Just recently I mentioned creating an order and I was bringing up our history of having payments arranged through invoicing in the past. After asking, I get a very negative toned response filled with a lot attitude and disrespect.  This was due to him being confused of what past invoicing could mean?  The corner bakery staff proceeds to try to belittle me for not saying "we have a house account" when I am clearing mentioning that we have paid invoices in the past.  I am confused at the immediate retaliation as I am just simply waiting to be questioned on anything from our past invoice. Later on he puts me on a hold after the order is made, as he was not looking to finalize things right then.  Another poor experience I have had was with our online order (via Grubhub).  The order arrived on time, but unfortunately there were several items we ordered that were not there.  I called customer service and was placed on periodic holds for an hour, even then I had to make several requests of getting our order fulfilled- as the first option they gave was to refund me and not deliver what was ordered. We wanted to make Corner Bakery Catering work, but there seems to be many internal issues and for that I would not recommend Corner Bakery catering to any businesses.
